<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-05-11T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-05-11T13:00:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/638a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-11T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 11,
                                        1927—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>216. The Nationalist News Agency (Chinese) publishes telegram dated
                            Hankow May 3, stating Asiatic Petroleum Company operating Changsha under
                            German management until its own representative now returning to Changsha
                            arrives.</p>
                        <p>American firms restive under trade stoppage and Department is interested
                            in any attempts of other nationalities to continue or reopen commerce
                            where Americans have evacuated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>